criteria.textblock:
        Inclusion Criteria:

          -  individuals aged ˃35 years and having ≥16 teeth diagnosed as chronic periodontitis

          -  not received any periodontal therapy within the previous 6 months;

          -  not received antibiotic/anti-inflammatory drug treatment within the previous 6 months.

        Exclusion Criteria:

          -  receiving medical treatment for cancer, rheumatoid arthritis, diabetes mellitus,
             cardiovascular disease, or any other systemic disease;

          -  being pregnant or being in the period of menopause or lactation;

          -  receiving any drug therapy that might affect the clinical characteristics of
             periodontitis;

          -  usage of systemic antimicrobials during the 6 weeks prior to data collection
